@startuml
title Viaverse Media Upload / CDN / Moderation — Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "media-service" as Media
database "S3 / Object Storage" as S3
participant "media-worker" as Worker
participant "moderation-service" as Moderation
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka

User -> Client : select media
Client -> BFF : POST /media/upload-sessions
BFF -> Media : createUploadSession(command)
Media -> DB : insert MediaAsset(PENDING_UPLOAD)
Media -> S3 : create presigned PUT
Media --> Client : upload URL + mediaId

Client -> S3 : PUT binary directly
Client -> BFF : POST /media/{id}/confirm
BFF -> Media : confirmUpload
Media -> Worker : enqueue processing job
Worker -> S3 : read original / write derivatives
Worker -> Moderation : scan media
Moderation --> Worker : approved/rejected/review
Worker -> DB : update APPROVED/REJECTED + derivatives
Worker -> Kafka : MediaApproved / MediaRejected

note bottom
Client uploads binary directly to object storage.
media-service manages session, metadata, processing, moderation and domain references.
end note
@enduml
